narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: The class was fairly relaxed, which was good, and the topics were interesting even as someone with minimal interest in microeconomics. Unfortunately, it was hard to stay engaged early on.
Really solid teacher but class could be organized a bit better with assignments and learning coding would be helpful for final project

comments: It was pretty much the same as it would have been otherwise, which is fine.

narratives.question_text:
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: If you need a chill econ seminar, go for it. The workload is low (two presentations and an exam), but do be prepared for the end of the semester to be busier.
